cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.LG 

The paper deals with 3D face reconstruction using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of bump mapping, which is a graphics technique and falls under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. The use of deep convolutional encoder-decoder networks for estimating bump maps falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper extensively tests and evaluates its approach, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
